Checklist:

**New docs**:
- [x] Add new "Developing apps in IntelliJ" page to the docs, mentioning:
  - [x] Setup and configuration (including system requirements, like version of Java, etc)
  - [x] Creating new projects
  - [x] Creating new projects from existing sources
  - [x] Editing source code and How to view and interpret "problems view" and the list of errors and warnings
  - [x] Running the app (in emulators and hardware)
  - [x] Debugging an app (in emulators and hardware)
  - [x] Hot Reloading and Restarting
  - [x] How to view device/emulator logs
  - [x] Observatory (basics of opening, and cross link to dart docs)
  - [x] How to file feedback/bugs
  - [x] How to upgrade the plugin(s)
  - [x] What the plugin doesn't do (and when to use flutter tool. e.g. upgrading Flutter?)
- [x] Add a link in the top-level menu to the new Developing... page under How-Tos

comment_data.body:
Regarding IDE integration, I don't think there's a good story for hosting plugin docs _within_ the IDEA help system FWIW.  (See this [support topic](https://intellij-support.jetbrains.com/hc/en-us/community/posts/206760095-how-do-i-plug-into-the-main-idea-help-system-).)

A good middle ground might be to add an action to open our docs to the top-level help menu:

![screen shot 2016-10-04 at 10 39 01 am](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/67586/19085371/f3910224-8a1e-11e6-86d7-8ce6ebb030ee.png)

Hopefully something on flutter.io?

We hosted the atom plugin docs separately from flutter (on github web hosting), but that didn't have a super coordinated experience w/ flutters docs.

flutter.io would be great.

@sethladd : thoughts, reactions?
I agree. Seth, is your docs process for flutter.io described somewhere?

Repo is here: https://github.com/flutter/website

Please send PR's and once merged, they get auto-deployed. Thanks!
I think we should also have an entry in the faq (flutter.io/faq) about editor choice and recomendations.

I updated the first entry in this bug to contain a checklist of all the changes I plan on making over the next two days. @devoncarew @pq @stevemessick @sethladd please review and see if you think I am missing something!
No obvious omissions from my perspective.
Added a few items. Good list!

I just ran into a problem that should not affect many people, but might be worth mentioning.

With the latest version you cannot continue working on a project that was created with an earlier version of the Flutter plugin. The problem is that we only recently started marking Flutter projects with a module type and old projects do not have that. The solution is to create a new project pointing to the same source directory, and overwrite existing files (.idea, *.iml). The symptom is that there is no device selector in the tool bar.

> With the latest version you cannot continue working on a project that was created with an earlier version of the Flutter plugin. 

Tracking bug filed: #341

Awesome.

Make @sethladd and @qchong happy and it works for me!
